description: {"blocks":[{"key":"95nou","text":"OBJECTIVES","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f9frp","text":"The primary objective of this study is:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"am2o4","text":"(a) to analyse Relative Telomere Length (RTL) in blood samples taken from patients during peri-operative chemotherapy for operable gastric or gastro-oesophageal junction adenocarcinoma. This will allow us to determine if the baseline (pre-treatment) RTL correlates with patient outcome as measured by relapse-free (RFS) and overall survival (OS).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c7a55","text":"The secondary objectives of this study are:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kcrb","text":"(a) to determine if the baseline (pre-treatment) RTL correlates with “tumour response” as measured by down-staging of the primary tumour with the pre-operative component of chemotherapy (comparison of the radiological staging at diagnosis, before pre-operative chemotherapy, with pathological staging at subsequent resection or with repeat radiological staging in the event of progressive disease so that the tumour is inoperable).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"76g8a","text":"(b) to analyse changes in markers associated with cellular senescence in blood samples taken from patients during peri-operative chemotherapy for operable gastric or gastro-oesophageal junction adenocarcinoma. These will include cathelicidin-related antimicrobial protein (CRAMP), EF-1a, stathmin, and chitinase 3-like protein 3.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1ibh7","text":"The tertiary (exploratory) objectives of this study are:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"98n97","text":"(a) to analyse changes in CK-18 in blood samples taken from patients during peri-operative chemotherapy for operable gastric or gastro-oesophageal junction adenocarcinoma as a marker of drug-induced cell death by apoptosis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ib8f","text":"(b) to analyse changes in senescence-associated micro-RNAs in blood samples taken from patients during peri-operative chemotherapy for operable gastric or gastro-oesophageal junction adenocarcinoma.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a1j5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4i92g","text":"STUDY DESIGN","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cj7sm","text":"This will be a multi-centre, open, non-randomised study. Eligible patients will be those with operable gastric, gastro-oesophageal junction or lower oesophageal adenocarcinoma who are about to undergo peri-operative chemotherapy with either the ECF/EOF or ECX/EOX (epirubicin, Cisplatin/oxaliplatin and capecitabine/5-FU) regimens. Additionally, patients randomised in the NCRN STO3 study to receive ECX + bevacizumab will also be eligible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
